ent-ClothingOuterArmorCPArmorMolle = MOLLE body armor
    .desc = A tactical vest with a modular attachment system that allows you to customize the harness for any mission. It combines basic ballistic protection with the ability to hang bags, pouches, and gear exactly where you need them.
    .suffix = HL2
ent-ClothingOuterArmorCPCivilProtectionVest = civil defense unit armor
    .desc = Standard Alliance protective gear. Combines a lightweight Kevlar base with tactical attachments for duty gear, providing a balance between protection and mobility.
    .suffix = HL2
ent-ClothingOuterArmorCPCivilProtectionVestCommissar = armor of the civil defense commissioner
    .desc = Enhanced protective gear for senior Civil Defense command personnel, featuring extended armor plates and distinctive green elements. It symbolizes not only increased survivability but also the Alliance's absolute authority on the streets.
    .suffix = HL2
ent-ClothingOuterArmorCPCivilProtectionVestDL = civil defense division leader armor
    .desc = Elite protective gear for senior Civil Defense officers, featuring enhanced ballistic protection and expanded system interfaces. Its distinctive silver color and tactical vest emphasize the Alliance's status as a divisional commander, making key operational decisions.
    .suffix = HL2
ent-ClothingOuterArmorCPCivilProtectionVestMed = civil defense medic armor
    .desc = A tactical uniform for civil defense medical personnel, combining light body armor, sterile pockets for medications, and patches with a cross on a red background. Its design balances rescue duties with the need to work in "administrative regulation" zones.
    .suffix = HL2
ent-ClothingOuterArmorCPTrenchcoat = civil defense officer's cloak-armor
    .desc = A distinctive element of the Civil Defense senior personnel uniform, combining the regulation cloak with built-in light body armor. Its elegant cut and signature blue color emphasize its administrative status without detracting from its readiness for operational intervention.
    .suffix = HL2
ent-ClothingOuterArmorCPTrenchcoatCommissar = civil defense commissioner's cloak-armor
    .desc = An elite version of the officer's uniform, the regulation cloak is combined with reinforced armor plates and green accents, symbolizing the highest administrative rank. Its appearance simultaneously demonstrates the inviolability of authority and a willingness to exercise personal "educational influence."
    .suffix = HL2
ent-ClothingOuterArmorCPTrenchcoatDL = divisional civil defense leader's cloak-armor
    .desc = The highest form of tactical and administrative gear, where the cloak is combined with a command-level flak jacket and red rank accents. This outfit symbolizes absolute authority over the assigned territory and the readiness to personally lead the suppression of any incidents.
    .suffix = HL2
ent-ClothingOuterArmorCPKevlarHeavy = kevlar body armor
    .desc = Lightweight and flexible armor made of multilayer aramid fibers, capable of stopping fragments and pistol bullets. It's the perfect balance between stealth and reliability for situations where tension plates would be useless.
    .suffix = HL2
ent-ClothingOuterArmorCPPlateArmor = tiled homemade vest
    .desc = A makeshift protection system assembled from scrap materials. Steel sheets, ceramic tiles, and thick fabric. It's crude, heavy, and unreliable, but sometimes capable of stopping a bullet where expensive armor is inaccessible.
    .suffix = HL2
ent-ClothingOuterArmorCPRebelArmorHeavy = rebel heavy body armor
    .desc = A set assembled from captured parts, decommissioned army armor, and homemade plates that speaks more of a will to resist than of actual protection. Worn with the knowledge that even symbolic armor is better than no armor at all in the face of the Alliance.
    .suffix = HL2
ent-ClothingOuterArmorCPRebelArmorLight = rebel body armor
    .desc = A homemade, reinforced suit of armor made from captured armor plates, steel, and ballistic fabric, assembled for those planning to survive the thick of conflict with the Alliance. Its weight is the price to pay for the chance to survive a direct hit from a standard Civil Defense weapon.
    .suffix = HL2
